{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> κλῖμαξ</b>, ᾰκος, ἡ, <br /> (κλίνω) <b>ladder</b> (because of its <b>leaning aslant</b>), [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “SIG” 1169.92 (Epid.)\">Refs</a>]; <b>scaling-ladder</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 3.23, 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Historia Graeca (Hellenica)” 7.2.7, etc.; κλίμακος προσαμβάσεις 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Septem contra Thebas” 466,compare 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Phoenissae” 489; κλιμάκων ὀρθοστάτας προσβαλών [prev. author] “Supp.” 497 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; προσθεῖναι Th.[same place]; <b>boarding-ladder, gangway</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Iphigenia Taurica” 1351, 1382, 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 22.30 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; κ. σκύτιναι, στύππιναι, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd-2nd c.BC: Philo Mechanicus “(Belopoeica) Excerpte aus Philons Mechanik - Ath. Berl. Akad.” 102.13, 16. \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <b>staircase</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 1.330, 10.558, +others, “IG” 22.463.46; κ. ξύλιναι [prev. work] 1668.84; κ. ἑλικτή\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] winding <b>stair</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC(?): Callixinus Historicus 1. \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>frame with crossbars</b>, on which persons to be tortured were tied, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Ranae” 618, “Comica Adespota” 422. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> <b>ladder used in reducing dislocations</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “περὶ ἄρθρων ἐμβολῆς” 42; κ. ἰσχυροὺς ἔχουσα κλιμακτῆρας [prev. work] 78. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> <b>wrestler's trick</b>, ἀμφίπλεκτοι κ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Trachiniae” 521 (Lyric poetry), compare 5th c.AD(?): Hesychius Legal icographus see at {ἐκ κλίμακος}. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__IV</b></Level2> in Rhet., <b>climax</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demetrius Phalereus Rhetor “Demetrius on Style” 270, 1st c.AD: Quintilianus Rhetor Latinus 9.3.54, 3rd c.AD: Longinus Rhetor 23.1 (_plural_). \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__V</b></Level2> <b>part of a chariot</b>, narrowing like steps, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD(?): Pollianus Epigrammaticus 1.253. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__VI</b></Level2> in <i>plural</i>, <b>handrails</b> on either side of a bridge, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Arrianus Historicus “Anabasis” 5.7.5. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]","strongNumber":"G8025","accentedUnicode":"κλῖμαξ","shortDef":"a stairway","mediumDef":"a stairway","stepGloss":"a stairway","stepTransliteration":"klimax","count":0,"_step_Type":"word"}]}